<subSubSection id="E2EF90ACFFE5BC1BCBF1F7AFCB300BBD" box="[151,264,1439,1466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA4AC327FFE5BC1BCBF1F7AFCB300BBD" blockId="8.[151,453,1403,1466]" box="[151,264,1439,1466]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">
(
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BCBF9F7AFCB380BBD" box="[159,256,1439,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Figure 6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2EF90ACFFE5BC1BCBF1F7D7CEC30822" pageId="8" pageNumber="583" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AA4AC327FFE5BC1BCBF1F7D7CEC30822" blockId="8.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis id="98811F35FFE5BC1BCBF1F7D7CB320806" bold="true" box="[151,266,1511,1537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species differs from other species of the genus in having the apex of the aedeagal shaft distinctly tapered beyond the preapical processes in posterior view and the preapical processes relatively long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2EF90ACFFE5BC1BCBA1F41FCB4009FD" pageId="8" pageNumber="583" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA4AC327FFE5BC1BCBA1F41FCB0D08B1" blockId="8.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis id="98811F35FFE5BC1BCBA1F41FCB69084E" bold="true" box="[199,337,1583,1609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Description</emphasis>
. Length of male 
<quantity id="6D0D6EC2FFE5BC1BC97BF41FC840084D" box="[541,632,1583,1610]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="583" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
. Natural coloration of only available specimen unknown due to DNA extraction from whole body, crown with two pairs of small spots on anterior margin, dorsum otherwise without distinct spots or larger maculae. Crown (
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BC93AF447C8890895" box="[604,689,1655,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
) slightly longer medially than next to eye, shorter than basal width between eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA4AC327FFE5BC1BCBA1F48FCB4009FD" blockId="8.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">
Male pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BCAC3F48FCBC408DD" box="[421,508,1727,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
) narrowly rounded apically, margin unmodified. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BCF80F48FCF0108DD" box="[1254,1337,1727,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
) slightly longer than maximum width, lateral margin evenly convex, apex forming slightly acute angle. Style preapical lobe acutely produced, apophysis slender and elongate without preapical angle, with seven rounded preapical teeth (
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BCE09F537CA800941" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BCA93F51BC8770941" box="[501,591,1835,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
) with dorsal apodeme relatively short and narrow, forming narrowly acute angle with dorsal margin of shaft; shaft relatively broad and very slightly tapered over most of length, more abruptly tapered at level of preapical processes and slightly sinuate distally; shaft in posterior view (
<figureCitation id="32CEDFA2FFE5BC1BCFFAF543CECC0989" box="[1180,1268,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1225,1249]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,525,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-166@8.[151,1436,525,1201]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Mayawa vestigia sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, base of abdomen, ventral view; D-E, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; F, styles, connective, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view (shaft broken); H, aedeagus, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556781/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="583">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
) parallel-sided basally, broadened at level of preapical processes, then tapered toward apex, preapical processes relatively long and strongly divergent from shaft, distal processes very short; gonopore very large, extended slightly basad of bases of preapical processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E2EF90ACFFE4BC1ACBA1F2A6CEBA0EB7" box="[199,1154,150,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AA4AC327FFE4BC1ACBA1F2A6CEBA0EB7" blockId="9.[151,1437,150,429]" box="[199,1154,150,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis id="98811F35FFE4BC1ACBA1F2A6CB700EB7" bold="true" box="[199,328,150,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name refers to the vestigial distal processes of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
